<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1073" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1073">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Loomis</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-08"><hi rend="italic">June 8,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 344.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 444, of the 17th ultimo, stating that Dr. Rojas Paul, a former
                            president of Venezuela, is anxious to preserve the Cuban citizenship of
                            an adopted daughter who is a native of that island.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have to say that the question will be one for the
                            determination of the Cuban authorities when a definitive government
                            shall be established in Cuba.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>